This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel meta reinforcement learning algorithm that learns a low-complexity neural objective function to improve generalization. The paper also uses off-policy second-order gradients during meta-training, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

The paper also touches upon several other sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with intelligent agents and their learning algorithms, cs.RO (Robotics) as it discusses the application of reinforcement learning in robotics, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks to learn the objective function, and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it mentions the use of RL algorithms in computer vision tasks. However, these sub-categories are less likely as they are not the primary focus of the paper.
